                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 811.0144/7.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to Chargé
                            <persName type="to">O’Shaughnessy</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-01-28T18:00:00-05:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">January 28, 1914, 6 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>629. Consul, Nuevo Laredo, reports that General Quintana states that he has
                    reported arrest of Cantú to General Tellez, Chief of Division at Monterey, and
                    is unable to release Cantú without orders from Tellez. Consul adds there is no
                    doubt about kidnapping.</p>
                <p>Bring to attention of appropriate authorities and renew demand for release of
                    Cantú.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Bryan</hi>
                    </signed>.</closer>
            </div>
        </body>
